So this is a middle English term for you.
这是中古英语中“你”的说法。

194
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:32,520
You.
你。

195
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,520
Yes.
是的。

196
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:34,520
Right?
对吧？

197
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,280
So can I say, I love thee?
所以我能说“I love thee”吗？

198
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:37,280
You could.
你可以。

199
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:38,280
That would be very romantic.
那会非常浪漫。

200
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:41,200
But also inappropriate for the office.
但在办公室就不合适了。

201
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,600
But it's very old English.
但这是非常古老的英语。

202
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:46,640
I guess if you're reading Shakespeare, you would definitely come upon this, right?
我想如果你在读莎士比亚，你肯定会遇到这个词，对吧？

203
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:47,640
Yes.
是的。

204
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:48,680
And what about wed?
那“wed”呢？

205
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:55,520
This is also an old word for, an old verb for the action of marrying someone.
这也是一个古老的词，一个古老的动词，表示结婚这个行为。

206
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:59,400
So I can say, we will be wed next year.
所以我可以这样说：我们明年将结婚。

207
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:02,400
But don't say that now because you'll sound quite silly.
但现在别这么说，因为听起来会很傻。

208
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,400
Yeah.
嗯。

209
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,400
It's too old-fashioned.
太老套了。

210
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,920
Yeah, I guess so.
嗯，我想也是。

211
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:10,080
But it's good to know, especially if you guys are reading something a little bit more classical.
但知道这些有好处，尤其是如果你们在读一些更经典的作品。

212
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:12,240
Or you plan to get married to an English person.
或者你打算和一个英国人结婚。

213
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,520
All right.
好的。

214
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:15,520
And our last phrase.
还有我们最后一个短语。

215
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:18,720
Wear it as a symbol of our love and commitment.
戴上它，作为我们爱与承诺的象征。

216
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:21,480
Wear it as a symbol of our love and commitment.
戴上它，作为我们爱与承诺的象征。

217
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:23,440
So now he's referring to the rings, right?
所以他现在指的是戒指，对吧？

218
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:25,960
Wear the ring as a symbol.
戴上戒指作为象征。

219
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:26,960
A sign.
一个标志。

220
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:27,960
A representation.
一种代表。

221
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:28,960
Yes.
是的。

222
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:30,200
Of love and commitment.
爱与承诺的象征。

223
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:33,480
So why would you wear a ring as a symbol of something?
那你为什么要戴戒指作为某物的象征呢？

224
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:37,800
Well obviously, you know, love, you can't see it, you can't touch it.
很明显，你知道，爱是看不见、摸不着的。

225
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:38,800
Right.
对。

226
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:41,040
So you need something to show you that it's there.
所以你需要一些东西来向你表明它存在。

227
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:42,720
So you need a sign of that love.
所以你需要一个爱的标志。

228
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,720
Something that you can see.
一些你能看到的东西。

229
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:45,080
So that's what the ring represents.
这就是戒指所代表的。

230
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:46,080
Yeah.
嗯。

231
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:48,120
But how about this word, commitment?
那“commitment”这个词呢？

232
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:49,680
A commitment is a strong promise.
承诺是一个强有力的誓言。

233
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:53,880
So you promise to love that person, to take care of them, etc.
所以你承诺爱那个人，照顾他们等等。

234
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:54,880
Yeah.
嗯。

235
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:55,880
Okay, great.
好的，很好。

236
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:59,680
So now we are a little bit more familiar with some of the language you hear in a wedding
所以现在我们对婚礼上听到的一些用语更熟悉了

237
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:01,400
ceremony.
仪式。

238
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:03,680
And we also know all of the names of the fingers.
而且我们也知道了所有手指的名称。

239
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:04,680
Exactly.
没错。

240
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:12,440
So why don't we listen to the dialogue one more time to hear these all in context.
那我们为什么不把对话再听一遍，在上下文中听听这些词呢？

241
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:23,480
The rings please.
请把戒指拿来。

242
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:30,840
May this ring be blessed so he who gives it and she who wears it may abide in peace and
愿这枚戒指被祝福，这样给予它的人和佩戴它的人都能在和平中安住，

243
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:35,160
continue in love until life's end.
并继续相爱，直到生命尽头。

244
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:42,920
And may this ring I be wed wear it as a symbol of our love and commitment.
愿我结婚时佩戴这枚戒指，作为我们爱与承诺的象征。

245
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:49,000
Honey, that's my pinky.
亲爱的，那是我的小指。

246
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:52,240
That ring goes on the ring finger.
那枚戒指应该戴在无名指上。

247
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:53,240
This one?
这根吗？

248
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:55,680
That's my index finger.
那是我的食指。

249
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:57,480
Oh, right.
哦，对。

250
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,480
This one, right?
这根，对吧？

251
00:09:58,480 --> 00:10:01,480
That's the thumb make.
那是大拇指。

252
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:04,320
Okay, I got it.
好了，我明白了。

253
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:06,160
This is the ring finger.
这是无名指。

254
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:08,000
That's my middle finger, Nick.
那是我的中指，尼克。

255
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:11,760
This is my ring finger.
这是我的无名指。

256
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:25,120
All right, so now it's perfectly clear and a romantic dialogue in the end.
好了，现在完全清楚了，最后还有一段浪漫的对话。

257
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,120
Yeah, very romantic.
嗯，非常浪漫。

258
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:28,040
Although a little bit embarrassing.
虽然有点尴尬。

259
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:29,040
Yeah.
嗯。

260
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,440
So what about wedding rings?
那结婚戒指呢？

261
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:31,960
Now we have different types of rings, right?
现在我们有不同类型的戒指，对吧？

262
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:37,120
We have the wedding ring, the one that we just heard, but we also have an engagement
我们有结婚戒指，就是我们刚才听到的那种，但我们还有订婚

263
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,120
ring.
戒指。

264
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:39,120
Yes, yeah.
是的，没错。

265
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:44,400
In most English speaking countries, the woman is very, very lucky because she gets two rings.
在大多数英语国家，女人非常非常幸运，因为她能得到两枚戒指。

266
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:49,920
So when the man asks her to marry him, he gives her a diamond.
所以当男人向她求婚时，他会给她一颗钻石。

267
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:50,920
A diamond ring.
一枚钻石戒指。

268
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:53,480
That is usually, that's the engagement ring.
那通常是订婚戒指。

269
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:57,040
And it's really, really important that he does this.
他这样做真的非常重要。

270
00:10:57,040 --> 00:11:00,160
And it's also really important that he spends a lot of money on the diamond.
而且他在钻石上花很多钱也非常重要。

271
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,840
Yeah, I know about this.
嗯，我知道这个。

272
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:02,840
Weddings are forever, right?
婚礼是永恒的，对吧？

273
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:03,840
Yes.
是的。

274
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:07,160
And the tradition is you must spend at least one month's salary.
传统是你必须花至少一个月的工资。

275
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:08,160
Wow.
哇。

276
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:09,160
Is that it?
就这样吗？

277
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:10,160
Yeah.
嗯。

278
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:14,520
So the girl gets a diamond engagement ring, and then on wedding day, she gets the wedding
所以女孩得到一枚钻石订婚戒指，然后在婚礼当天，她得到结婚

279
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:15,520
ring.
戒指。

280
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:16,520
Yes.
是的。

281
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:17,720
And usually, will she wear both of them?
通常，她会两枚都戴吗？

282
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:19,400
Yeah, she'll always wear both of them.
嗯，她会一直两枚都戴。

283
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:23,920
So the engagement ring goes closest to you, and then the wedding ring on top.
所以订婚戒指戴在最靠近你的位置，然后结婚戒指戴在上面。

284
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:26,920
And the engagement ring, it represents?
订婚戒指代表什么？

285
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:29,520
The commitment to marry her.
娶她的承诺。

286
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:32,560
No, wait, the commitment from the man to marry her.
不，等等，是男人娶她的承诺。

287
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:34,840
Okay, so it's a symbol that they will get married.
好的，所以这是一个他们会结婚的象征。

288
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:37,080
Yes, it's a symbol of the promise.
是的，这是承诺的象征。

289
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:40,880
Now what happens if they break up and they don't get married?
那如果他们分手了，不结婚了怎么办？

290
00:11:40,880 --> 00:11:41,880
Does he get the ring back?
他能拿回戒指吗？

291
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:43,560
I don't know.
我不知道。

292
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:46,260
Okay, here's the rule.
好的，规则是这样的。

293
00:11:46,260 --> 00:11:50,640
If he was a jerk, no.
如果他是混蛋，就不行。

294
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:53,800
But if it was sort of like a happy breakup, then okay.
但如果算是和平分手，那就可以。

295
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:54,800
Okay.
好的。

296
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,720
I guess it's a big risk, right?
我想这是个很大的风险，对吧？

297
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,720
Yeah.
嗯。

298
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,720
All right.
好的。

299
00:11:58,720 --> 00:11:59,720
That's it for today, guys.
今天就到这里吧，各位。

300
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:02,120
Let us know if you guys have any interesting wedding stories.
如果你们有任何有趣的婚礼故事，请告诉我们。

301
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:08,200
I know that sometimes weddings can be embarrassing, people, I don't know, objecting, maybe I've
我知道有时候婚礼会很尴尬，比如有人反对，或者我见过新郎晕倒。

302
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,800
seen the groom faint.
甚至掉进游泳池。

303
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:10,800
Or even fall in a pool.
掉进游泳池。

304
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:12,320
Fall in a pool.
掉进游泳池。

305
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:15,120
So if you have any stories, please share them with us.
所以如果你们有故事，请和我们分享。

306
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:16,560
Come to EnglishPod.com.
来EnglishPod.com。

307
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:20,720
And also if you have any questions or doubts, Erica and I are always there to answer them.
另外，如果你们有任何问题或疑问，我和Erica随时都在那里回答。

308
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,620
Well thanks for listening to this lesson, everyone.
好了，感谢大家收听这节课。

309
00:12:22,620 --> 00:12:29,680
And until next time, goodbye.
下次再见，拜拜。
